(:kind :chapter :book "Reference Manual" :chapter-number 14 :title "Chapter 14 — The five-gate dispatcher" :source-path "git://origin/main/scheme-books/reference/14-the-five-gate-dispatcher.md" :size 3851 :sha256 "35d4c8f08652a0c8" :content "---\nslug: sakura-scheme-book-reference-14\ntitle: The five-gate dispatcher\nbook: reference\nchapter: 14\nof: 16\npart: II\napp: scheme-repl\npalette: book-standard\ncanonical: true\nowner: docs-team (Lane 6)\nphilosopher-lens: [popper, wittgenstein-late]\nstatus: draft\nlast-reviewed: 2026-07-12\nprev: 13-the-fuel-budget\nnext: 15-the-verb-registry\n---\n\n# Chapter 14 — The five-gate dispatcher\n\nEvery verb call passes through five gates before it runs. This is\nthe safety geometry of Sakura Scheme.\n\n> **Sakura says**\n>\n> Nothing runs without permission. Five checks in order. If any\n> refuses, the whole call refuses. The refusal is legible — I can\n> tell you which gate said no.\n\n## The five gates\n\n```sakura-scheme\n(define (dispatch call ctx)\n  (or (tier-gate call ctx)         ;; tier allowed?\n      (capability-gate call ctx)   ;; surface allowed?\n      (registration-gate call ctx) ;; verb registered?\n      (fuel-gate call ctx)         ;; fuel available?\n      (custom-gate call ctx)       ;; verb-specific check\n      (run call ctx)))             ;; all clear — run\n```\n\nEach gate returns either a `refuse` record (with a reason) or `#f`\n(pass). If any gate returns a refuse, the whole dispatch returns\nthat refuse.\n\n## Gate 1 — Tier\n\n```sakura-scheme\n(define (tier-gate call ctx)\n  (let ([verb-tier (verb-tier call)]\n        [caller-tier (operator-tier ctx)])\n    (if (tier-allows? caller-tier verb-tier)\n        #f      ; pass\n        (refuse :gate 'tier\n                :caller caller-tier\n                :verb-tier verb-tier\n                :message \"operator tier does not permit this verb\"))))\n```\n\nThe color tier canon: white / pink / green / light-purple / deep-\npurple. A free-tier operator can't call a magic verb.\n\n## Gate 2 — Capability\n\n```sakura-scheme\n(define (capability-gate call ctx)\n  (let ([verb-caps (verb-required-caps call)]\n        [surface   (current-surface ctx)])\n    (if (surface-has-caps? surface verb-caps)\n        #f\n        (refuse :gate 'capability\n                :verb call\n                :surface surface\n                :missing verb-caps))))\n```\n\nSome verbs need network, some need camera, some need audio. If the\nsurface doesn't have the cap, the verb is refused. This is how\n`open-camera` on a headless server correctly fails at dispatch\nrather than runtime.\n\n## Gate 3 — Registration\n\n```sakura-scheme\n(define (registration-gate call ctx)\n  (if (registered? (verb-name call))\n      #f\n      (refuse :gate 'registration\n              :verb (verb-name call)\n              :message \"verb is not registered\")))\n```\n\nA verb the engine doesn't know exists is refused before anything\ntries to compute it. Book of Words ch 3 covered this from the user\nside; this is the engine implementation.\n\n## Gate 4 — Fuel\n\nChapter 13 covered this. The dispatcher checks fuel BEFORE running\nso the operator's clock doesn't burn on a call that would refuse\nanyway.\n\n## Gate 5 — Custom\n\nVerb-specific gates. `charge` might need auth; `delete-shop` might\nneed a confirmation dialog completion; `send-money` might need a\nKYC state.\n\n```sakura-scheme\n(register-verb 'charge\n  :gate (lambda (call ctx)\n          (if (authenticated? ctx)\n              #f\n              (refuse :gate 'custom\n                      :verb 'charge\n                      :message \"authenticate first\"))))\n```\n\n## The refusal record\n\nEvery refuse produces a SLAT record:\n\n```sakura-scheme\n(refuse\n  :gate     'tier\n  :verb     'magic-optimize\n  :caller   'free\n  :message  \"operator tier does not permit this verb\"\n  :suggest  'upgrade-to-imagine)\n```\n\nSakura reads it and produces the human reply per Book of Words ch 12\n(register + hedge + short).\n\n## Cross-links\n\n- [[book-of-reference]] ch 15 — the verb registry.\n- [[book-of-reference]] ch 13 — fuel budget.\n- [[book-of-don-ts]] — refusal register from her side.\n\n---\n\nTurn the page.\n")
